Package it.polimi.ingsw.model.exceptions

Class JullPointerException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • it.polimi.ingsw.model.exceptions.JullPointerException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class JullPointerException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown when attempting to access a value in a JSON file by using a key not present in the current scope of the file. As the name suggests, it is a mask for the famous NullPointerException but with two key differences:
    * Its causes are somewhat always known, since it can only generate while reading from a JSON file using a non-existent key.
    * It is a checked exception, allowing the use of a try/catch block without falling in the bad practice of catching runtime exceptions.
    In case of failed management of this exception, or unexpected missing value, a new runtime exception, JsonException, is thrown.
    See Also:
    JsonException, Serialized Form
